definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype where disease is present.

label.value: decreased extent of host-defense induced lesion by host hypersensitive response

definition.value: A phenotype where the process of host tissue cell death causing a host lesion is induced by the host activating its own hypersensitive response in defense to a lesser extent than normal.
This term is to be used for host protection against the pathogen.
A single species phenotype where the morphology of a cell is abnormal.
A single species phenotype where the morphology of a cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).
A single species cell morphology phenotype where the length of hyphal filaments are normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).
A single species population phenotype affecting the morphology of a colony of unicellular individuals.

Note that colony morphology terms are not used in PHIPO to annotate filamentous-form colonies because these phenotypes can be related to specific growth terms for hyphal colony morphology please search for PHIPO:0001214 (hyphal growth phenotype). For unicellular colony morphology at the usual resolution it is usually not possible to make any statement about an individual. For dimorphic pathogens these terms are suitable for yeast-form colony phenotypes.
An individual organism growth phenotype in which the size or extent of directional growth of hyphae is normal.
Although this phenotype is for an individual it can be inferred from a population in a colony.
An individual organism growth phenotype in which the growth of hyphae is decreased.
Although this phenotype is for an individual it can be inferred from a population in a colony.
An individual organism growth phenotype in which the growth of hyphae is abolished (it was present and is now absent).
Although this phenotype is for an individual it can be inferred from a population in a colony.
A single species growth phenotype which affects or involves normal or abnormal size, extent or rate of directional growth of the hyphae of an individual organism.
An individual organism growth phenotype in which the size or extent of directional growth of hyphae is abnormal.
Although this phenotype is for an individual it can be inferred from a population in a colony.

A growth phenotype which describes the change or absence of change of individuals or populations (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a nutrient stimulus.
A growth phenotype which describes the sensitivity, resistance or absence of change of individuals or populations after exposure to a specific stress.
A growth phenotype which describes the sensitivity, resistance or absence of change of individuals or populations after exposure to a specific chemical.
A growth phenotype which describes the absence of change of individuals or populations after exposure to voriconazole (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).
A phenotype that affects any physical object quality, such as morphology, number, location, etc., of an individual, tissue, cell, or cellular component.

label.value: abnormal anatomical structure physical quality phenotype

definition.value: A physical anatomical structure phenotype in which the amount, distribution, morphology, or other physical characteristic of a cell part, cell, or tissue, or individual is abnormal in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.
A single species cell phenotype that consists of the cell's disposition to survive and develop normally.
A single species phenotype where the morphology of an organism is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).
A single species metabolic cellular process phenotype, in which the occurrence of a pathogen effector preventing the hydrolysis of chitin by chitinases is decreased (chitin hydrolysis is increased).
A single species metabolic cellular process phenotype, in which a pathogen effector does not prevent the hydrolysis of chitin by chitinases.

label.value: decreased level of host defense-induced reducing sugar in apoplast

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype, in which the level of host produced reducing sugars usually present in the apoplast during infection is lower than normal.

label.value: increased level of host defense-induced reducing sugar in apoplast

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype, in which the level of host produced reducing sugars usually present in the apoplast during infection is higher than normal.

label.value: pathogen reactive oxygen species production within host present

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype, in which the level of pathogen produced reactive oxygen species (ROS) usually present during infection is present as normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: presence of pathogen tissue to tissue migration within host

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction colonization phenotype in which the ability of the pathogen to move directionally from tissue to tissue within the host organism is present.
A pathogen host interaction phenotype, in which the host phenolic compounds usually present during infection are normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).
A pathogen host interaction phenotype, in which the host RNA usually present during infection is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).
A pathogen host interaction phenotype, in which the level of pathogen RNA usually present during host infection is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: pathogen inhibition of host defense induced acidification in phagolysome

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype where the host induced pH decrease within the host phagolysome in response to pathogen colonization is inhibited.
An individual organism growth phenotype in which the growth of hyphae is increased.
Although this phenotype is for an individual it can be inferred from a population in a colony.

label.value: host defense-related RNA involved in a pathogen interaction present

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype, in which the host defense-related RNA usually present during infection is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: effector-mediated suppression of host effector triggered immunity absent

definition.value: A phenotype where the process of host tissue cell death causing a host lesion initially induced by the host activating its own hypersensitive response in defense, is subsequently not suppressed by a pathogen effector.

label.value: effector-mediated suppression of host PAMP-triggered immunity absent

definition.value: A cell signaling pathway phenotype where the molecular pattern-induced host innate immune response signaling pathway is not suppressed by a pathogen. (GO:0052034)
A single species molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of chitinase activity is increased.

label.value: pathogen inhibition of host defense induced alkalization

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype where the host induced pH increase in response to pathogen colonization is inhibited.
A pathogen host interaction phenotype where the host induces a pH increase in response to pathogen colonization.
A single species molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of chitinase activity is decreased.

label.value: pathogen binding of chitin with host present

definition.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the binding of chitin or chitin fragments by the pathogen during host colonization is present.

label.value: pathogen binding of chitin with host absent

definition.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the binding of chitin or chitin fragments by the pathogen during host colonization is absent.

label.value: increased number of pathogen asexual sporulation structures within host lesion

definition.value: A pathogen reproductive phenotype within host in which the frequency of occurrence of asexual sporulation structures within a host lesion is greater than normal.

label.value: increased protein phosphorylation involved in host PAMP-triggered immunity (MAPK) signaling activated by pathogen

definition.value: A host immune system signaling pathway pathogen-host interaction phenotype observed during the activation of host PAMP-triggered immunity in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: host PAMP-triggered immunity activated by pathogen present

definition.value: A phenotype where the process of pathogen-associated molecular pattern (PAMPs) or microbe-associated molecular pattern (MAMPs), activate the host PAMP-triggered immunity (PTI) innate immune system to trigger host defense responses such as reactive oxygen species (ROS) and callose deposition is present. (PAMPs and MAMPs are conserved structures among microbial species, eg chitin and lipopolysaccharide (LPS)).

label.value: pathogen modulation of host metabolic process phenotype

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype, in which a pathogen effects a change in the metabolic processes of its host organism.

label.value: pathogen modulation of chitin hydrolysis by host present

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype, in which a pathogen effector preventing the hydrolysis of chitin by host chitinases is present.
A single species metabolic cellular process phenotype, in which a pathogen effector prevents the hydrolysis of chitin by chitinases.

label.value: abnormal host structure induced by pathogen

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype where the development of a host structure is abnormal during pathogen infection.
A pathogen host interaction phenotype, in which the host protein usually present during infection is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: decreased pathogen tissue to tissue migration within host

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction colonization phenotype in which the ability of the pathogen to move directionally from tissue to tissue within the host organism is decreased.

label.value: host immune system inflammatory response activated by pathogen present

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype where the host immune system inflammatory response during pathogen infection is present. (GO:0006954 inflammatory response).

label.value: decreased host immune inflammatory response with pathogen

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype where the host immune system inflammatory response during pathogen infection occurs to a lesser extent than normal. (GO:0006954 inflammatory response).
